The paper deals with unsupervised image registration using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a bottleneck autoencoder to encode population-level information of deformation fields, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of smoothness-based regularization and population-based regularization, which are techniques used in optimization and numerical analysis (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT).
